						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							New Control : Fading Slide Show
							Thursday, July 22, 2004 - 5:18:47 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I created a new Control that will allow you to create a fading slide show.&nbsp; I got the idea from&nbsp; <A href="http://www.shadowedstrife.net">http://www.shadowedstrife.net</A>&nbsp; who has it on their guild wizard site (it`s on the right side).&nbsp; Like any other control, you create it in the Control Editor and select Slide Show Control from the Control Type List.</P>
<P>A few things you should be aware of:&nbsp; </P>
<OL>
<LI>When you Add images to the slide show, the list is NOT SAVED until you click the Save button.&nbsp; Just because it`s in the grid, doesnt mean it will be saved, so please remember that.&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>You really should have all the images the same size.&nbsp; You can resize images in pretty much any image editor.</LI>
<LI>The fade effect doesnt work in Mozilla browsers, but the control itself should (images should change on time etc)</LI>
<LI>You can select the duration of each image being shown by selecting the desired duration from the list.&nbsp; Default is 3 seconds.</LI></OL>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Fixed login cookie, Submit template function
							Friday, July 16, 2004 - 11:29:06 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I fixed the login cookie issue from before.&nbsp; You dont have to login everytime you visit now, which was pretty annoying.</P>
<P>I added a <STRONG>Submit Your Template</STRONG> function to allow people who like making templates, to be able to share them with other guilds.&nbsp; It doesn`t just submit the stylesheet, it submits all your control positions, the images attached to them, it basically clones your look/feel.&nbsp; After you submit a template, and after its approved, other guilds can use your template.&nbsp; So, if you have design skills, use em, and share em :)</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Todays Guild Wizard Patch
							Thursday, July 15, 2004 - 11:22:25 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>Today`s patch added a new Control type, and added edit support for existing controls.. as well as a few bug fixes:</P>
<UL>
<LI>New control: <STRONG>Embeded Page - </STRONG>This control creates a Custom Page that embeds another web-sites content in it.&nbsp; For example, lets say that you want to have a page that has a live video feed from another service you can simply specify the URL (address) of the page, give it an ID, and the guild wizard system will create a custom page for you.&nbsp; Create a button for it (it automatically adds the custom page to your links list in the Control Editor too), and you are all set.</LI>
<LI>You can now Edit all Custom Controls that you create.&nbsp; Pretty self explainatory in the Control Editor.&nbsp; Click the edit icon for the item you want to edit, and away you go.</LI>
<LI>There is a new style element for the forum message page.&nbsp; The column that holds the avatar is now able to be styled in the Style Editor.&nbsp; You can give it a different background color, border etc.</LI>
<LI>I fixed a problem with the Delete Private Message button.. it was only deleting the first message.&nbsp; Its working correctly now.</LI></UL>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Dude, two upgrades in one day??
							Monday, July 12, 2004 - 11:58:09 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>Well, you can tell that I am not playing any MMORPGs at the present time :)&nbsp;&nbsp; I spent tonight doing some nice tweaks on the new style editor, based on a couple peoples suggestions (and a few peoples whining/death threats) hehe</P>
<OL>
<LI>When you adjust the width of the Left or Right panel, the Center panel`s margin will automatically adjust accordingly.&nbsp; So, if you make the left panel width 400pixels, the Center panel will automatically have a 400pixel margin.&nbsp; Good suggestion whoever sent it to me. 
<LI>I fixed a little bug when you type in a URL for the background image of stylesheet item.&nbsp; Before it was always assuming the image was in your guilds image directory, which is fine for most cases but I can see it would irritate an advanced user wanting to use an image on their own webserver.. so the system will check if a valid URL is entered, if not it defaults to look for that image in your guilds directory. 
<LI>Ok those who styled their guild site entirely with the visual editor is going to hate me when they read this.&nbsp; You can now copy style settings between elements to ensure a consistent look/feel throughout your elements.&nbsp; For advanced users, its still easier to just hop into the stylesheet and cut/paste the style settings, but for normal users this is going to save a LOT of time.<BR><BR>Example:&nbsp; Lets say you want all your grid headers to look the same as your Roster header.. no problem now.&nbsp; Just select Roster Header from the new dropdownlist to Copy From, and then select the Raid List Header, for example.&nbsp; Click the Copy To button and the Raid List Header automatically inherits the style settings for the Roster Header.&nbsp; Rinse and Repeat for the various other elements that build the grids, and you have a consistent look/feel without having to remember colors, borders, font-sizes, padding, margins etc.&nbsp; Just remember, you can *still* customize it after you inherit a style, its just a base to work with.<BR><BR>This is going to save a lot of time for button styling too.. design your first buttons style, and then copy the style to all your other buttons.. </LI></OL>
<P>Thanks for all the suggestions from the various guild leaders / web masters out there.&nbsp; I really appreciate the help to make Guild Wizard better.&nbsp; Believe me guys/gals, I am on your side.. if you want something added, changed, altered, or removed.. let me know!&nbsp; </P>
						</p>
					
